Need For Speed (2014) Film
Fresh from prison, a street racer who was framed by a wealthy business associate joins a cross country race 
with revenge in mind. His ex-partner, learning of the plan, places a massive bounty on his head as the race begins.
Need for Speed is a 2014 American 3D action film directed by Scott Waugh, written by George Gatins and John Gatins
and produced by DreamWorks Pictures. It stars Aaron Paul as street racer Tobey Marshall,who sets off to race cross-country,
as a way of avenging his friend's death at the hands of a rival racer. The film was released by Touchstone Pictures 
on March 14, 2014, in 3D, IMAX, and conventional 2D theaters.The storyline, in particular, the cross country racing and settings
in countryside rather than cities,is loosely based on Need for Speed: The Run, Need for Speed: Hot Pursuit and Need for Speed: Rivals
The film grossed $203 million internationally, against a $66 million production budget.
